title: The fall of the Caliphate
description:
A brief history of the events leading up to the fall of the Caliphate and the disastrous after-effects; the willful genocidal attacks on the Muslim nations lead by the west; principally Britain and France, later the United States to secure land and resources. A book accompany this short film which explains the subversive techniques deployed by the west and various spies working within Muslim countries to gain and retain a strong foothold.

Egypt | Iraq | Qatar | 1500 min | Released

Drama | History

Director:
Mohamed Azizya
|
Written by:
Yousry El Gendy |
Release Date: 11 August 2010
